how to set up stanford's vpn on the ipad stanford answers stanford university stanford answers how to set up stanford's vpn on the ipad categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home how to set up stanford's vpn on the ipad search this site to set up stanford's vpn on the ipad tap the settings icon tap general tap network tap vpn tap add vpn configuration tap ipsec use the description field on this screen to label the configuration with a unique identifier for example stanford public vpn then enter the following information server su vpn stanford edu account your sunet id password your sunet id password group name stanford note the capital s secret call 5 help and ask for the vpn shared secret key tap the save button in the upper right corner of the screen to return to the vpn selection screen your new configuration should be selected by default if more than one configuration exists you may need to tap the new entry for stanford to select it a check mark displays next to the active configuration you can activate the vpn on this screen by tapping the on off switch or you can return to the home screen by pressing the home button tap settings and then tap the vpn on off switch on the main settings screen if the vpn connection is successful you will receive a welcome message stanford public vpn service unauthorized access is prohibited you can return to the settings screen and tap the switch again to disable the vpn ipad at stanford stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
